cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on full-duplex networks and investigates power control strategies to improve the performance of the network. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of power control on the performance of full-duplex networks, which involves the transmission and processing of information. This falls under the scope of information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses power control strategies to mitigate interference and improve the performance of the network, which involves control of the system. This falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of the network in terms of area spectrum efficiency and energy efficiency, which are important metrics for multimedia applications. This falls under the scope of multimedia. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions the minimum self-interference cancellation capability required to guarantee the performance of cell-edge users, which involves security and privacy concerns. This falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
